18/09/2005
NEW YORK, United States -- US Undersecretary of State for Political Affairs Nicholas Burns reaffirmed his country's support for the NATO bids of Adriatic Charter signatories Albania, Croatia and Macedonia during a meeting in New York on Friday (16 September). Afterwards, Croatian Foreign and EU Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic told reporters that she did not hear Burns mention any dates, suggesting he had not commented on rumours about suspending plans for NATO enlargement until 2008. (Vecernji list - 17/09/05; HINA - 16/09/05)
